Package uk.ac.ljmu.fet.cs.csw.CompetitiveMinesweeper.gui

Class GUIHelper

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.ac.ljmu.fet.cs.csw.CompetitiveMinesweeper.gui.GUIHelper
  • public class GUIHelper
extends Object
    This class offers automation on launching a GUI and an AI in parallel to each other. The class also offers linking the GUI and the AI together.
    Author:
    "Gabor Kecskemeti, Department of Computer Science, Liverpool John Moores University, (c) 2019"

      The interface allows customising the creation of a SimpleGamePanel
      private static class  GUIHelper.SimpleLaunch
      This class offers an implementation of the GUIHelper.LaunchGUI interface on the simplest way possible: directly calling the constructor of SimpleGamePanel.

      • launchCompetitor

        static MineMap launchCompetitor​(Class<? extends GameSolverThread> comp,
                                GUIHelper.LaunchGUI mygui,
                                MineMap base,
                                int pushright,
                                int pushdown,
                                boolean scale)
                         throws InstantiationException,
                                IllegalAccessException,
                                IllegalArgumentException,
                                InvocationTargetException,
                                NoSuchMethodException,
                                SecurityException
        Clones a map, instantiates an AI and configures its GUI, launches the AI's solver thread. If there are issues with instantiating the solver class, there could be all kinds of exceptions thrown.
        Parameters:
        comp - The class of the AI solver.
        mygui - The launcher for the GUI to be created.
        base - The base map to solve
        pushright - how many windows should we go to the right
        pushdown - how many windows should we go towards the bottom
        scale - Do we want to allow the GUI to scale its grid size based on the minemap's column and row numbers?
        Throws:
        InstantiationException
        IllegalAccessException
        IllegalArgumentException
        InvocationTargetException
        NoSuchMethodException
        SecurityException
